event: response.reasoning_summary_text.done
data: {"type":"response.reasoning_summary_text.done","item_id":"rs_09ef032a1c16c5d1016a04984749c08196a3117f1530878f63","output_index":0,"sequence_number":98,"summary_index":0,"text":"**Calculating train meeting time**\n\nI’m working on a classic problem involving two trains: Train A leaves Paris at 3 PM heading to Lyon, while Train B leaves Lyon at 4 PM heading to Paris. They start 470 km apart. A travels 80 km in the first hour, leaving 390 km to close after B starts. From there, they're closing in at 180 km/h. It takes about 2 hours and 10 minutes after 4 PM for them to meet, which will be at 6:10 PM."}

