event: response.output_text.done
data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","content_index":0,"item_id":"msg_09ef032a1c16c5d1016a049851f1bc81968028c3164b6f9c65","logprobs":[],"output_index":1,"sequence_number":404,"text":"Train A (Paris→Lyon) leaves at 3:00 at 80 km/h. In the hour 3:00–4:00 it goes 80 km, so at 4:00 the remaining distance = 470 − 80 = 390 km.\n\nAfter 4:00 they approach each other at 80 + 100 = 180 km/h. Time to meet after 4:00 = 390 / 180 = 13/6 h = 2 h 10 min.\n\nMeeting time = 4:00 + 2:10 = 6:10 PM.\n\nDistance from Paris = total time A traveled × 80 = (3 h 10 min = 19/6 h) × 80 = 80·19/6 = 760/3 ≈ 253.33 km.\n\nAnswer: They meet at 6:10 PM, about 253 1/3 km from Paris."}

