event: response.completed
data: {"type":"response.completed","response":{"id":"resp_09ef032a1c16c5d1016a049846dbd481968420c232f3da434c","object":"response","created_at":1778686022,"status":"completed","background":false,"completed_at":1778686035,"error":null,"frequency_penalty":0.0,"incomplete_details":null,"instructions":null,"max_output_tokens":1024,"max_tool_calls":null,"model":"gpt-5-mini-2025-08-07","moderation":null,"output":[{"id":"rs_09ef032a1c16c5d1016a04984749c08196a3117f1530878f63","type":"reasoning","summary":[{"type":"summary_text","text":"**Calculating train meeting time**\n\nI’m working on a classic problem involving two trains: Train A leaves Paris at 3 PM heading to Lyon, while Train B leaves Lyon at 4 PM heading to Paris. They start 470 km apart. A travels 80 km in the first hour, leaving 390 km to close after B starts. From there, they're closing in at 180 km/h. It takes about 2 hours and 10 minutes after 4 PM for them to meet, which will be at 6:10 PM."},{"type":"summary_text","text":"**Confirming distance and calculations**\n\nI calculated that 3 hours and 10 minutes is approximately 3.1667 hours, which equals 19/6 hours. Multiplying that by 80 km/h gives a distance of about 253.333 km from Paris. Alternatively, after 4 PM, Train A travels for an additional 2.1667 hours, covering around 173.333 km plus the initial 80 km, confirming the total distance as approximately 253 km and 333 meters. The meeting time was confirmed at 6:10 PM, and I'll briefly show these steps for clarity."}]},{"id":"msg_09ef032a1c16c5d1016a049851f1bc81968028c3164b6f9c65","type":"message","status":"completed","content":[{"type":"output_text","annotations":[],"logprobs":[],"text":"Train A (Paris→Lyon) leaves at 3:00 at 80 km/h. In the hour 3:00–4:00 it goes 80 km, so at 4:00 the remaining distance = 470 − 80 = 390 km.\n\nAfter 4:00 they approach each other at 80 + 100 = 180 km/h. Time to meet after 4:00 = 390 / 180 = 13/6 h = 2 h 10 min.\n\nMeeting time = 4:00 + 2:10 = 6:10 PM.\n\nDistance from Paris = total time A traveled × 80 = (3 h 10 min = 19/6 h) × 80 = 80·19/6 = 760/3 ≈ 253.33 km.\n\nAnswer: They meet at 6:10 PM, about 253 1/3 km from Paris."}],"role":"assistant"}],"parallel_tool_calls":true,"presence_penalty":0.0,"previous_response_id":null,"prompt_cache_key":null,"prompt_cache_retention":"in_memory","reasoning":{"effort":"medium","summary":"detailed"},"safety_identifier":null,"service_tier":"default","store":false,"temperature":1.0,"text":{"format":{"type":"text"},"verbosity":"medium"},"tool_choice":"auto","tools":[],"top_logprobs":0,"top_p":1.0,"truncation":"disabled","usage":{"input_tokens":62,"input_tokens_details":{"cached_tokens":0},"output_tokens":710,"output_tokens_details":{"reasoning_tokens":448},"total_tokens":772},"user":null,"metadata":{}},"sequence_number":407}

